  "excerpt": "<p>Getting Started with Metrics Glossary DataTools for Salesforce demonstrates how to build a dictionary for the most important metrics within your organization.</p>",
  "content_html": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-wideleft\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/salesforce-metrics-glossary\" title=\"Salesforce Metrics Glossary\">DataTools </a>metrics analyst for Salesforce will organize your organizations metrics and KPIs. To automate the analysis and requirement gathering process we have created Metric Analyst AI enabled tool that reverse engineers your self service analytics into smart documentation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To utilize the metrics analyst AI feature, you will first click on the &#8220;Magic&#8221; icon. You will then perform the following 3 steps to recieve recommendations</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"#step1\" title=\"Select and analyze salesforce dashboards\">Step 1: Select and Analyze your dashboard(s) and related reports</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"#step2\" title=\"Analyze your Salesforce dashboards\">Step 2: Analyze your Dashboards</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"#step3\" title=\"Generate your metrics glossary\">Step 3: Generate your Metrics Glossary</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"#4\" title=\"Review Recommendations\">Review Recommendations</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"#add\" title=\"Add metric to glossary\">Add Metric to Glossary</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#ignore\" title=\"Ignore metric\">Ignore the Recommendation</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#merge\" title=\"Merge Metrics\">Merge Metrics</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#noaction\" title=\"No Action\">Take No Action</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#complete\" title=\"Complete your metrics Analyst Session\">Completing your Metrics Analyst Session</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"899\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-19-899x1024.png\" alt=\"Automated Salesforce Metrics Glossary\" class=\"wp-image-9141\" style=\"width:307px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-19-899x1024.png 899w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-19-263x300.png 263w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-19-768x875.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-19.png 962w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 899px) 100vw, 899px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Administrating DataTools Pro Metrics Analyst</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-3 gb-3-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Data Processing</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Metrics Analyst AI processes your salesforce dashboard and report data together to produce a metrics glossary.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Open-AI Integration </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>DataTools Pro Metrics Analyst services are designed to handle meta data from DataTools Pro. The final step to process and prepare recommendations utilizes a combination of traditional analytical computations built by our team and multi-step AI reasoning powered by Open AI. Data processed by OpenAI is disabled for retention and training and we do not use any OpenAI memory or retention capabilities.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Disabling Metrics Analyst &#8211; Coming Soon</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the event your organization has a policy or restrictions on using 3rd party AI services like OpenAI, you can disable metrics analyst feature from your DataTools Pro account. We are planning to enable a simpler version of Metric Analyst that does not include reasoning and analysis but still provides significant time savings reverse engineering your dashboards using traditional computational methods.</p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 1: Select and Analyze your dashboard(s) and related reports</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>1. Select the Salesforce dashboard that you would like to analyze. The free DataTools Pro app supports 1 dashboard at a time. We are adding multiple dashboard analysis and consolidation features in team version of DataTools Pro.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f4f9f8\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"680\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-2-1024x680.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9405 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f4f9f8; width:283px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-2-1024x680.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-2-300x199.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-2-768x510.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-2-1536x1020.png 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-2.png 1784w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>2. Click the &#8220;Analyze Dashboards&#8221; button to process your selected dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f5faf9\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-3-1024x311.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9406 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f5faf9; width:404px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-3-1024x311.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-3-300x91.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-3-768x233.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-3-1536x467.png 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-3.png 1777w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Click &#8220;More Info&#8221; to expand and review the processed reports or dashboards. The links will launch your report or dashboard into Salesforce</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f5f8f9\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f5f8f9;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-4-1024x482.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9407 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-4-1024x482.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-4-300x141.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-4-768x361.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-4-1536x723.png 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-4.png 1692w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"step2\"><strong>Step 2: Analyze your Dashboards</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In the Metrics Analyst header, click &#8220;Step 2: Analyze Dashboards&#8221;. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"b1ded0\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"904\" height=\"171\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-5.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9408 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #b1ded0; width:341px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-5.png 904w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-5-300x57.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-5-768x145.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 904px) 100vw, 904px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This process will review your dashboards and supporting reports and build a standardized model of the the widgets that can be transformed into metrics definitions. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Select &#8220;More info&#8221; to expand and view the definitions for your widgets. You can optionally remove any widget form your list for further processing.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f6f6f7\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"510\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-6-1024x510.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9409 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f6f6f7; width:363px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-6-1024x510.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-6-300x149.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-6-768x383.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-6-1536x765.png 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-6.png 1782w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"step3\"><strong>Step 3: Generate your Metrics Glossary</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Click Step 3: Generate your Metrics Glossary to execute a multi-step batch process that evaludates the metadata processed in step to along with a number of other meta data points not displayed to calculate then reason a list of recomended metrics.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Minimizing Metrics Analyst during batch processing</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f6f9f8\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"560\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-9-1024x560.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9412 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f6f9f8; width:323px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-9-1024x560.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-9-300x164.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-9-768x420.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-9.png 1086w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Because the final step is a batch process, it can take 20 seconds to 1 minute to complete processing. You can minimize metrics analyst and continue to work on the same metrics glossary page viewing and updating metrics. When the metrics analyst completes it will maximize itself so you can complete the final step.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"aae0ce\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"596\" height=\"144\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-8.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9411 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #aae0ce; width:296px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-8.png 596w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-8-300x72.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 596px) 100vw, 596px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"step4\"><strong>Review Recommendations</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The final step is to review recommendations and take action on the metrics</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"add\">Add Metric to Glossary</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are two ways to add a metric to the Metrics Glossary:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Select the checkbox next to all metrics and then click on the &#8220;Add Button&#8221;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click on the &#8220;+&#8221; button located to the left of the suggested metric.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f1f3f3\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"949\" height=\"605\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-10.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9413 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f1f3f3; width:275px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-10.png 949w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-10-300x191.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-10-768x490.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 949px) 100vw, 949px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"ignore\">Ignore the Recommendation</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To ignore a recommendation, click on the &#8220;-&#8221; button. This will remove it from the list and DataTools Pro will keep track of ignore metrics for future enhancements to your metrics analyst. Currently the ignore recommendations operates to de-clutter the recommendations so you can focus only on metrics that you want to add to your dictionary</p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"noaction\"><strong>Take No Action</strong> &#8211; Another way to ignore recommendations is simply to leave it in the recommendations list. This </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"merge\">Merge Metrics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Select one or multiple recommended metrics that you would like to merge. You can merge two recommendations together by selecting the checkbox to both metrics, then clicking merge, you can choose to merge the metrics with each other or with a single metric that already exists in your glossary</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"eef1f0\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"690\" height=\"715\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-11.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9414 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #eef1f0; width:277px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-11.png 690w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-11-290x300.png 290w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Select the metric that you would like to either create and merge or merge into.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"e8f1ee\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"831\" height=\"894\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-14.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9417 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #e8f1ee; width:350px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-14.png 831w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-14-279x300.png 279w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-14-768x826.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 831px) 100vw, 831px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Merging a metric will add the recommended name as an &#8220;Alias&#8221;.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"complete\">Completing your Metrics Analyst Session</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Upon clicking &#8220;Complete&#8221; Metric Analyst will prompt you for feedback. Feel free to give your honest feedback. This information is currently setup to go back to our team so we know what is working and what isn&#8217;t. Because our product team and analysts cannot see your actual meta data, the more details on what went right or wrong the better.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"ebf0ef\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"774\" height=\"679\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-15.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9418 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #ebf0ef; width:284px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-15.png 774w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-15-300x263.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image-15-768x674.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 774px) 100vw, 774px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n"
}